									<p class="text_type_v4 mg_t5">
										<span class="color_pink">STEP 1.</span> If you are dismissed from your current place of employment, register yourself as a jobseeker at the WorkNet site, and take your ID card to your local employment center to apply for unemployment.
									</p>
									<p class="text_type_v4 mg_t5">
										<span class="color_pink">STEP 2.</span> At the employment center, fill out and submit an application for unemployment benefits.
									</p>
									<p class="text_type_v4 mg_t5">
										<span class="color_pink">STEP 3.</span> You will be notified whether or not your application has been approved. (Rejection notices are delivered in writing)
									</p>
									<p class="text_type_v4 mg_t5">
										<span class="color_pink">STEP 4.</span> To be registered as unemployed, visit your local job center on the designated dates, which are set at one-week to four-week intervals.
									</p>
									<p class="text_type_v4 mg_t5">
										<span class="color_pink">STEP 5.</span> Submit the following to the employment center: status of unemployment for the acknowledged duration of unemployment, and proof of job seeking activities (Submit resumes, job interviews, etc.)
									</p>
								</section>
